body: I can help taking a look if there's a reproducible script.  Currently it's still RC so we can fix it if there's a bug.
@trivialfis I think https://github.com/onnx/sklearn-onnx/blob/master/tests_onnxmltools/test_xgboost_converters.py should be perfect for this
Alright.  Will take a look later tonight.  Thanks for the link!

Got it.  In a recent commit we set all default parameters of `def __init__()` to `None`, in order to remove the duplication of default values between Sklearn interface and XGBoost core.  This breaks the converter that relies on `get_param` returning a valid value.

@victornoel Is it safe to assume users call this function only after `fit` or `load_model`?  If so we can call `save_config` inside `get_params` and obtain a complete list of internal parameters: https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/saving_model.html#saving-and-loading-the-internal-parameters-configuration

@trivialfis you mean calling the `convert_sklearn`/`convert_xgboost` functions?

Yes, it is meaningless to convert an unfitted model IMHO, so users should have a model that is already fitted.

After a fix for the above error, I still got an:

> RuntimeError: Options ['zipmap'] are not registerd for model 'XGBClassifier'.

I'm not sure what it's.  But I passed the test in regressor by a fix.  Will make a PR on XGBoost later.
